        <h1>Privacy Policy for Gotcha</h1>
        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> October 20, 2025</p>

        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Gotcha</strong> collects, uses, and protects user information. By using the app, you agree to the practices described in this policy.</p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>a) Non-personal information</h3>
        <p>We may collect non-identifiable information such as device type, operating system version, country, language settings, and general gameplay statistics.</p>

        <h3>b) Advertising information</h3>
        <p>Gotcha uses <strong>advertising services</strong> (e.g., Google AdMob) that may collect your <strong>Advertising ID</strong> to display relevant ads. You can reset or disable this ID in your Android settings.</p>

        <h3>c) In-app purchases</h3>
        <p>In-app purchases are processed through <strong>Google Play Billing</strong>. We do not collect or store payment information — all transactions are handled securely by Google.</p>

        <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>We use collected information to improve gameplay experience and performance, display relevant ads, fix technical issues, and support optional features such as rewards or achievements.</p>

        <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>Gotcha may use the following services:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Google AdMob – for displaying ads</li>
            <li>Google Play Billing – for purchases</li>
            <li>Google Play Games Services – for leaderboards and achievements</li>
        </ul>
        <p>See Google’s policy here: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a></p>

        <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect user information, but no system is completely secure.</p>

        <h2>6. Children’s Privacy</h2>
        <p>Gotcha is not directed to children under 13 years old. If you believe your child has provided personal information, contact us and we will delete it.</p>

        <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will appear on this page with a new “Last updated” date.</p>

        <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> milestone.artwork@gmail.com</p>
